Defendant in custody.
On count 5, fleeing an officer, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.
The defendant is eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The defendant has credit for 210 days.
On count 7, possess THC, the defendant is sentenced to three (3) months incarceration, concurrent with the prison sentence imposed on count 5 of this case.
The Court orders the court costs on this count be paid as a condition of extended supervision on count 5.
Minutes.

Defendant in custody.   
Count 5 - Fleeing an Officer - Guilty plea.   
Count 7 - Possess THC - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1,2, 3, 4, 6,8. & 9.  Motion granted.   
Count 5 - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseing as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
7) Six (6) months jail, consecutive to the sentence defendant is presently serving.   Seventy-five (75) days, under the Huber Law, up front.   One hundred five (105) days stayed, to be imposed by the agent.  Court will authorize travel out of county for purposes of employment.  
8) Submit DNA sample.  
In addition, defendant's operating privilege is revoked for six months.   
Count 7 -Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) year.   Conditions of probation are the same with the exception of jail time.  
Minutes.
